While his other "Saturday Night Live" cast mates, Chevy Chase and Dan Aykroyd, turned down the film, Belushi split his week between the movie set and the show. When the movie became a hit, Belushi left "SNL" for a film career, starring in three other films, including "The Blues Brothers," before he was found dead in 1982 from a drug overdose at the age of 33.
